				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Illusion Item: Amulet of Necropotence<a name="52887"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 20 04 5:57 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span> The first illusion mask I got was the DE mask. I was told the effect could change my faction in some evil zones to the point I wouldn't be KoS. So I got it and sure enough I could walk around in Neriak, Oggok and even OT evil city (before I spent too much time in KC). This became quite handy for making spell runs for evil alts as a Bard can get around much faster than SK's and Necro's. It also improved vision which was helpful at times.
<br />

<br />
 The next mask I camped was the Ikky mask. Rumor was it increased regen. It turns out I was misinformed about the regen. (even to this day I will see people claim it increases regen) It could change your faction in some parts of Kunark to where you won't be KoS to Iksar. Didn't seem very useful to me so i sold it and to my surprise it was worth quite a bit of plat so I farmed it heavily the next month. 
<br />

<br />
 Next illusion item I got was Lute of the Howler. As I'm sure you know gives a nice melee buff, haste,atk and str. Very useful item. I wish I could get the buff without the illusion cause its actually looks stupid.
<br />

<br />
 Lastly was Flayed Barbarian Hide mask. The illusion can give you the ability to Slam. Not real useful to Bards as we have other ways to interupt casters but could be used as a last resort. However I didn't get this mask for the illusion. The stats are incredible, the best droppable Bard mask by far.
<br />

<br />
 So yes I have illusion items but only useful ones. The water elemental illusion gives enduring breath but seems like a lot of trouble for an effect that could be easily gotten eslewhere.
<br />

<br />
 Even if you think the illusion looks cool doesn't it get old fairly quick? 
<br />

<br />
 Hey look at me I'm a Halfling weeee. Did you notice I'm Halfling? Halflings can't be Bards you know. Isn't it impressive?
<br />
How come nobody cares I'm a Halfling(.
<br />

