<br />
Illusion masks, aside from a few benefits here and there, such as EB, slam, shrink/grow, etc are not useful.  But, they are a bit of a status symbol, and can be a lot of fun.  Is it soething you need? no.  It is something that you can do in your off time.
<br />

<br />
Trust me, they get addicting.  You get one or two, no biggie, few more, the interest goes up, until eventually you get the crazy idea to get all of them, and then it gives you something to work on religeously.
<br />

<br />
If you cant see the uses for them, then ya need to open up a bit, and have a little more fun with them.  Aka when you go to pull, change your illusion before returning, make fun of your friends likes and dislikes of races, just change the monoteny of what your toon looks like.  
<br />

<br />
You say getting the illusions, use them for a while and they get old, well, consider that atleast you have the option to change what you look like, other than a chanter, rogue and bards, all other toons are stuck to what they are born with, and a few other options (crown of deceit, AoN).
<br />

<br />
Also, as far as your kids idea, I am 28.  And no, not all mine were useful by any means.
<br />

